row.column:
In Acumatica ERP, you can personalize your account, workspace, document processing, and data representation in ways to make using the system easier. You can specify your preferences for email signature, and dashboards. Other users will not be able to view your personal settings.{br}

 Acumatica ERP provides you with standard actions that you can use on many forms (such as exporting tables to Excel workbooks and attaching files to records) or even anywhere in the system (such as searching). {br}

In this topic, you will read about various system-wide actions and ways of personalizing Acumatica ERP to your needs.{br}{TOC}
==Access to Acumatica ERP==
To access the system, you identify yourself by typing your username and password when you sign in to the system. You can use your internal Acumatica ERP credentials, your domain credentials (if a system administrator of your organization has integrated Acumatica ERP with Active Directory), or your account credentials with an external identity provider, such as Google or Microsoft Account (if a system administrator of your organization has configured single sign-on with these providers).{br}

If you use Acumatica ERP credentials to access the system, your system administrator can allow you to change your password any time you want during your work with the system. If you forget your password or login, you can recover them if your system administrator has turned on this ability for you.{br}

Although it is a system administrator who initially fills in information about user accounts, you can change the parameters of your account without contacting the administrator. For example, you can specify or change your first and last name and your email address.{br}

You can sign in to different company branches (or even different companies) in different tabs of the same window or different windows of the same browser. After you finish working with the system, you should sign out to prevent unauthorized access to your account.{br}

For more information about access to Acumatica ERP, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Access|Accessing an Acumatica ERP Instance].
==Settings of Your Working Environment ==
 Acumatica ERP provides you with tools for personalizing your working environment to make it more convenient for you. You can configure the following parameters:[anchor|#_ec41eae0-fafa-4380-8281-5d1b7e404467]
*Time zone
*Locale settings (date, time, and number formats)
*Home page
*Favorite forms
For details about settings of your working environment, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Workspace|Managing Your Acumatica ERP Working Environment].
==Document Processing Settings==
In Acumatica ERP, you can set up certain parameters that affect your work with documents. If you have to sign PDF documents that you create in the system with a digital signature, you can use your personal certificate instead of the general certificate that is specified by your system administrator.{br}

If you send emails in Acumatica ERP, you may need to configure your signature, which you can do in your user profile.{br}

For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Personal_Document_Processing|Personalizing Document Processing].
==Personal Tasks and Events==
In the system, you can easily access tasks and events that were assigned to you. You can see the number of assigned tasks and events in the info area (for details, see [HelpRoot_Interface\Info_area|Info Area] in the Acumatica ERP Interface Guide) and open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000]) or [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404100|EP404100]) form for more details. If a reminder is configured for a task or event, you will be notified about the coming task or event in advance. For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Tasks_Events|Managing Your Tasks and Events].
==Data Presentation==
 Acumatica ERP stores and displays large data loads, and you may want to make this data convenient for view and analysis. To solve this task, you can filter data in reports and tables, and save filters for later usage. You also can adjust table view—for example, widen or constrict column widths and change column order. For details, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Personalize_Data_Representation|Personalizing the Presentation of Data ].
==Personal Dashboards==
Multiple dashboards can be created in Acumatica ERP by your system administrator or other colleagues who have appropriate rights. You can personalize these dashboards to view exactly the information you need if your system administrator allowed you to do so. For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Dashboards|Configuring Dashboards].
==Mobile Device Management==
If you are using the Acumatica mobile app, the information about the devices that allow push notifications from the app (within the settings of the particular mobile device) is stored in your Acumatica ERP user profile. The first time you sign in to the mobile app on a particular mobile device, the application sends details about your device to Acumatica ERP, and then the information is updated (if needed) with each subsequent sign-in. You can remove from the list of devices a device that you are no longer using or that you have lost. Also, you can control to which devices you allow the system to send push notifications.
==System-Wide Actions==
In Acumatica ERP, you can use standard actions that are available in multiple places of the system. If you need to, you can attach files (for example, scanned documents) and notes (for example, processing instructions for a document) to records. You can search for forms, help topics, or records if you want to quickly find these system entities.{br}

When you create new documents and objects in Acumatica ERP, you can fill in all document elements from scratch, copy and paste an existing document or object of the same type, or use a previously created template. The copy-and-paste options and templates make the creation process much easier for you and help you minimize input errors.{br}

When you work in Acumatica ERP, you may need to export data in formats that can be opened by external applications, such as Microsoft Excel. To solve this task, you can export data to Excel and CSV formats. The import operation from these formats is also supported. This support is useful, for example, when you have some data in Excel and want to load it in Acumatica ERP for further processing.{br}

If sometimes you need to transfer generic inquiries from one Acumatica ERP instance to another, you can use export and import of data in XML format.{br}

For more information about system-wide actions, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_System_Wide_Actions|Using System-Wide Actions].
==User Interface==
Employees on different positions use different sets of forms in Acumatica ERP to perform their work tasks. You can configure the user interface so that forms and reports you use frequently are at hand. If your user role provides you with access to multiple functional areas (such as Payables, Receivables, and Sales Orders) but you use forms in particular areas more often than in other areas, you can configure workspaces in the main menu so that the system displays only frequently used workspaces there. Similarly, you can configure each workspace to which you have access. To the Quick Menu, you can add only forms that you use more often.{br}

For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Presonalize_User_Interface|Personalizing the Modern User Interface].
==Documents Approval==
Your organization can reduce the time required for document assignment and routing because the system provides automatic assignment for all the required approvals. In Acumatica ERP the process of document approval can be enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] form. Acumatica ERP provides a single form, [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_50_30_10|Approvals] ([~/?ScreenId=EP503010|EP503010]), that can be used as a starting point for all documents that require approval. {br}

For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\CO__con_Centralized_Approvals|Approving Documents].

The first thing you do when you want to work with Acumatica ERP is signing in to the system. Because the financial information with which you work in Acumatica ERP is highly confidential, system administrators of your organization create user accounts and provide them with access rights. You can use one of these accounts to access the system.{br}
