To make your work more effective, Acumatica ERP provides you with tools that help you to organize your tasks and events, which you can create and manage in the system.{br}
In this topic, you will read about accessing your tasks and events, and adding reminders.{br}{TOC} ==Your Tasks and Events== The '''My Tasks and Events''' menu, located in the info area (upper-right corner of the screen; see [HelpRoot_Interface\Info_area|Info Area] in the Interface Guide), offers you a quick way to access the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404100|EP404100]) forms.((({S:Hint}The '''My Tasks and Events''' menu appears on the screen if the functionality is enabled for your Acumatica ERP instance by your system administrator. For details, see [HelpRoot_Administration\WebConfig__how_MyTasksAndEvents|To Turn On the My Tasks and Events Button] in the Acumatica ERP Installation Guide. ))) The '''My Tasks and Events''' menu button displays the total number of active tasks and events assigned to the current user, with a value in parentheses that indicates the number of new tasks and events. The numbers of new tasks and events are also displayed separately in the '''Tasks''' and '''Events''' command names.{br}
The system updates the information displayed on the '''My Tasks and Events''' menu every 10 seconds, so you can view the most current information about your tasks and events. A new task or event created in the system causes the following values to increase:[anchor|#ul_y4b_ggx_f3] *The total value (if you added the task or event) *Both the total and new values (if the task or event was added by any other means)
For details about work with tasks, see [[#_0d9864a6-c8db-4c65-b40a-a8f55ddc5990|Keeping Track of Your Tasks]. For more information about events, see [[#_fdd8a378-d080-4924-a257-d8cdca1fba21|Keeping Track of Your Events].{br}
For an important task or event, you can configure a reminder. In this case, for affected users, the '''Reminder''' button in the info area will blink at the time you specify, and the '''Reminder''' dialog box will appear (for details, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__ref_Reminder_Dialog_Box|Reminder Dialog Box]), informing them about all tasks and events that require their attention. For more information about reminders, see [[#_3a8c565c-8ca1-4068-8dc4-8dbb0f954fb4|Using Reminders].[anchor|#_0d9864a6-c8db-4c65-b40a-a8f55ddc5990] ==Keeping Track of Your Tasks== The [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000]) form displays the list of tasks assigned to you. By using this form, you can view tasks, drill down to the details of a task, and complete or cancel a task.{br}
To open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] form, do the following:[anchor|#ul_gvx_b4y_m3] *On the '''My Tasks and Events''' menu, click '''Tasks'''.
The [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] form displays the tasks you have created and all the tasks in your scope. For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\EP__con_Task_Management|Task Tracking Options].{br}
Depending on the default filter set for the form (if one has been set), you may see all active tasks or the most urgent ones. If a filter has been used, the filter name appears in the '''Select Filter''' box on the table toolbar (upper right). For more information about filters, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Personalize_Data_Representation|Personalizing the Presentation of Data ].{br}
You can click any task in the list to view or edit the details of the task. For more information, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\EP__con_Task_Management|Task Management].[anchor|#_fdd8a378-d080-4924-a257-d8cdca1fba21] ==Keeping Track of Your Events== An event is an activity with a specific starting time and duration. The [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404100|EP404100]) form displays all events associated with your user name. By using this form, you can do the following:[anchor|#_289777d7-f1a2-4acc-a145-9527414368d2] *View events *Drill down to the details of an event *Complete an event *Cancel an event *Export an event or your entire calendar with all events
To open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] form, do the following:[anchor|#ul_v5k_1ql_n3] *On the '''My Tasks and Events''' menu, click '''Events'''.
Depending on the filter set for the form (if one has been set), you might see all active events or only specific ones. If a filter has been applied to the list of events, the '''Select Filter''' box on the table toolbar (upper right) displays the filter name.{br}
You can click any event in the list to view or edit the details of the event. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\EP__con_Notifications_About_Events|Notifications About Events].[anchor|#_3a8c565c-8ca1-4068-8dc4-8dbb0f954fb4] ==Using Reminders== In Acumatica ERP, you can set reminders to alert yourself and other users about tasks and events that require attention or are overdue.[anchor|#_cf1acff2-a1c6-4c12-8a5f-812d28697473]((({S:Hint}Before you can start using reminders, you must ask your system administrator to enable the reminder functionality. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\Configuring_reminders|To Turn On Reminders] in the Acumatica ERP Installation Guide. ))) You can set up reminders for a task or an event, as described in [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\Reminders__how_Setup|To Set Up Reminders for Tasks and Events].{br}
At the time you have specified, the '''Reminder''' dialog box for the activated task or event will appear on the Acumatica ERP page you are using. You can cause the reminder to snooze (disappear and then reappear at a later time) or dismiss the task or event.{br}
Additionally, you can view the &ldquo;snoozing&ldquo; tasks and events in the '''Reminders''' dialog box which you can open by clicking the Reminder ([anchor|#image_crv_3cg_ps][image:UserGuide/Images/Reminders_Button.png|12px]) button in the info area.{br}
For more information about '''Reminder''' and '''Reminders''' dialog boxes, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__ref_Reminder_Dialog_Box|Reminder Dialog Box] and [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__ref_Reminders_Dialog_Box|Reminders Dialog Box]. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Tasks_Events|Managing Your Tasks and Events] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__mng_Personalize_Data_Representation|Personalizing the Presentation of Data ] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_40|Event and Task Categories] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204040|EP204040]) *[HelpRoot_Administration\EP__con_Notifications_About_Events|Notifications About Events] *[HelpRoot_Interface\IB_Filters|Filters] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\EP__con_Task_Management|Task Management] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\Reminders__how_Setup|To Set Up Reminders for Tasks and Events] *[HelpRoot_Administration\WebConfig__how_MyTasksAndEvents|To Turn On the My Tasks and Events Button] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404100|EP404100]) *[HelpRoot_Interface\Info_area|Info Area] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__ref_Reminder_Dialog_Box|Reminder Dialog Box] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__ref_Reminders_Dialog_Box|Reminders Dialog Box] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000])

With the task management capabilities of Acumatica ERP, you can keep personal to-do lists, configure reminders for all tasks or only the most important ones, track tasks assigned to you, create tasks, assign tasks to other users, and follow up on tasks assigned to others. These capabilities help you do the right things at the right time, so you can improve your performance and efficiency. ==Tasks== Each task has a ''creator'' and an ''assignee'': The task&rsquo;s creator is the employee who created the task, and its assignee is the employee to whom the task is assigned. (The creator and assignee may be the same employee.) A task should be assigned before it is saved. {br}
Tasks can be created as associated with no specific entity, or they can be created as associated with any of the following entities: leads, contacts, opportunities, business accounts, cases, employees, and projects. You can create such an association by using one of the following methods: [anchor|#ul_vvr_gf3_xp] *Specifying a related entity by using the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_20|Task] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306020|CR306020]) form when you create a new task or adjust an existing one *Creating a task by using the '''Activities''' tab on the corresponding data entry form. For instance, to create a task that will be associated with a certain case, you would use this tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_00|Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306000|CR306000]) form. {br}
When creating a task, the creator can configure a reminder for it and specify on what day before the due date the assignee should receive the reminder. On the specified date, the reminder will appear in the info area of the assignee&rsquo;s screen and will be blinking or highlighted in red until either of the users, the creator or the assignee, completes the task or changes its status.[anchor|#_dc9ef50a-a476-4656-9ce7-25c77573bf8e]((({S:Hint}Before you can start using reminders, you must ask your system administrator to enable the reminder functionality. For more information, see [HelpRoot_Administration\Configuring_reminders|To Turn On Reminders] in the Acumatica ERP Installation Guide. )))[anchor|#_b3f37502-4193-474e-9f21-d496e84ea2fc][anchor|#_399d3984-395b-4e87-8fdb-ddc152167d1c] ==Task Tracking Options== You can view the total number of your tasks and events, including the new ones, in the info area at the top of any Acumatica ERP form. The '''Tasks''' link opens the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000]) form. By using this form, you can view the following tasks: [anchor|#ul_qzr_fj3_xp] *Those you have created. If these tasks are assigned to other users, you might want to track them to see whether they are being fulfilled (and what related activities have been created for the tasks). Such tasks are displayed on the '''Follow-Up Tasks''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000]) form. *Those assigned to the users in your workgroup. *Escalated tasks assigned to users of workgroups that are positioned, in the company tree, on levels lower than your workgroup but in the same node. ((({S:Hint}You can hide a task, event, or other activity from external users by marking it ''Internal'' on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_20|Task] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306020|CR306020]), [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_30|Event] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306030|CR306030]), or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_10|Activity] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306010|CR306010]) form, respectively. ))){br}
To make the most important tasks noticeable to you at a glance, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_40|Event and Task Categories] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204040|EP204040]) form to associate different colors with different categories of tasks. For example, if you select red for the most important tasks, yellow for less important tasks, and green for normal tasks, you will see the tasks marked by exclamation marks (in the column with the '''!''' heading) highlighted with the respective colors. {br}
Tasks do not require approvals; they are completed by the assignees or canceled by the creators. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Organization\EP__con_Company_Organizational_Chart|Company Tree and Workgroups] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_10_00|Leads] ([~/?ScreenId=CR301000|CR301000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_20_00|Contacts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR302000|CR302000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_30_00|Business Accounts] ([~/?ScreenId=CR303000|CR303000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_40_00|Opportunities] ([~/?ScreenId=CR304000|CR304000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_00|Cases] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306000|CR306000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_20_40_61|Company Tree] ([~/?ScreenId=EP204061|EP204061]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000])

You can set up reminders for tasks and events that are important for you and whose end date you do not want to miss. Depending on whether you are setting up a reminder for a task or an event, you use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404000|EP404000]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_20|Task] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306020|CR306020]) forms or the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] ([~/?ScreenId=EP404100|EP404100]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_30|Event] ([~/?ScreenId=CR306030|CR306030]) forms. For more information about tasks, events, and reminders, see [HelpRoot_GettingStarted\IB_My_Tasks_and_Events_Panel|Your Tasks and Events ].{br}
In this topic, you will read about how to set up a reminder. ==To Set Up Reminders for Tasks and Events==[anchor|#ol_qx3_bl5_l3] #Open the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_40_00|Tasks] or [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_40_41_00|Events] form. #Click a task or event. #On the '''Details''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_20|Task] or [HelpRoot_FormReference\CR_30_60_30|Event] form, select the '''Reminder''' check box. #In the '''Remind at''' boxes, enter the date and time when the reminder goes into effect. #On the form toolbar, click '''Save'''.
For a task, the reminder will be in effect from the specified date and time until task completion or cancellation. The task reminder will be visible to the user to whom the task has been assigned. {br}
An event reminder, which is visible to the event creator and all potential attendees, is in effect from the specified date and time until you dismiss the reminder for this event.

When you work in Acumatica ERP, you may need to adjust data on forms that you use to solve your work tasks. You can filter data on forms, adjust data representation in tables, and filter data in reports, as described in this chapter. ==In This Chapter==[anchor|#_779e874a-e4dd-4ffa-9fcb-9445188a391f] {| class="checklist invisiblechecklist" | width="100%" |- | [anchor|#_432b9019-6ff1-4523-b915-e5904a4f7410] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__con_Personalize_Data_Representation|Data Presentation in Acumatica ERP] *[HelpRoot_GettingStarted\GS__con_Creating_Advanced_Filters|Creation of Advanced and Ad Hoc Filters]
